xplaining results, build testing and monitoring framework.</li> <li>Work in tandem with engineer team to link predictive mode output into our existing internal system and customer UIs.</li> <li>Help build out our Data Science team and platform inside an exciting start-up company with huge market potentials around the world.</li> </ul> <br />Requirements:<br /><br /><ul> <li>Bachelor's degree in Statistics, Computer Science, Engineering, or a similar field. Higher degrees in related fields is a plus.</li> <li>Fluent in Spanish and English.</li> <li>3+ years of related, practical experience, enterprise BI experience is a plus.</li> <li>Internal or external consulting experience in BI or analytics related areas.</li> <li>Experience in enterprise data warehouse solutions and ETL process.</li> <li>Experience in at least one of the following languages: Python, R, Scala. Java, Javascript, HTML, Django experience is a plus.</li> <li>Academic or professional experience with statistical models and modern machine learning methods.</li> <li>Knowledge of the practical data modeling pipeline, including data parsing, cleaning, hashing, and feature engineering. Understanding of predictive modeling process, including model evaluation, version control, monitoring and refresh.</li> <li>Understanding of distributed system concepts and experience working in Apache Hadoop, Hive or Spark is a plus.</li> <li>Ability to prioritize with good multitasking skills.</li> <li>Must be able to perform in a fast environment, can carry out work individually while maintain good team work spirit.</li> </ul> <br /><strong>Primary Location</strong>: South America, different country options available.<br /><br /><br /></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Numeric has been representing Analytics Professionals to our client companies since 1999. Recognized for excellence in Analytics Staffing, Numeric is well-known throughout the United States for providing niche talent. The Numeric advantage 